        <hi rend="italic">Der Morgen</hi>
      </head>

      <div>
        <p>Radical democratic daily Viennese
          newspaper, edited by Carl Colbert, editor also of <title level="j">Der Abend</title> (Evening)
          (1914&#x2013;18), who used the pseudonym "Alpheus," and whose wife Toni was one of
          Schenker's pupils. The paper was founded in 1910, and closed down on May 1, 1920, citing
          increased costs and the difficulty of conducting journalism in the current political
          climate. Click on <ref cRef="entity-000137">Colbert (family)</ref>.</p>

      </div>
